snippet.textDisplay: I'm originally from Palestine, and I heard this song on the radio this morning.  The beat of this song captivated me in so many ways, and until I heard "Mustafa, Mujtaba, Khatimo ilMorsaleen, ya Rahmaton lil Alameen"  I said to myself that these are Arabic words!  The song has to be intended to Prophet Muhammed peace be upon him, and indeed I fell in love with this song!!  Wonderful song from our Pakistani brothers.  It would help if I can get the translated lyrics to understand the whole song.  Keep it up!
snippet.textOriginal: I'm originally from Palestine, and I heard this song on the radio this morning.  The beat of this song captivated me in so many ways, and until I heard "Mustafa, Mujtaba, Khatimo ilMorsaleen, ya Rahmaton lil Alameen"  I said to myself that these are Arabic words!  The song has to be intended to Prophet Muhammed peace be upon him, and indeed I fell in love with this song!!  Wonderful song from our Pakistani brothers.  It would help if I can get the translated lyrics to understand the whole song.  Keep it up!
